        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 4:07PM EDT by NWS Cleveland OH</headline>
        <description>At 407 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Loudonville, or 15 miles southeast of Mansfield, moving east at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Loudonville, Glenmont, Nashville, Butler, Perrysville, and North
Liberty.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
